cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

This paper is about weakly supervised semantic segmentation using image labels. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques, which suggests that cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of prior knowledge and attention mechanisms, which are common themes in artificial intelligence (AI) research (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the generation of class-specific segmentation masks, which is a topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) (cs.CL). Finally, the paper presents experiments on the PASCAL VOC 2012 dataset, which is a widely used benchmark in multimedia (MM) research (cs.MM).
